Package org.example

Class MyArrayList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.example.MyArrayList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - this array stores in itself elements of type T.
    public class MyArrayList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    MyArrayList is a resizable array implementation in Java. MyArrayList grows dynamically. It has the following methods: get element by index; add element; remove element by index; insert element by index; clear array; quick sort method.

        Sorts the elements of the array in O(N*logN) time. This method is using a recursive algorithm.
        Type Parameters:
        T - object that should implement interface Comparable.
        Parameters:

        low - first index of the array to be sorted.
